Cleaning the Data

#Cleaning little details like parentheses and apostrophes that are present in the default data. These symbols need to be removed for R to use the columns in any commands.

WildlifeStudy$Common <- str_replace_all(WildlifeStudy$Common, "\\(.*", "")
WildlifeStudy$Common <- str_replace_all(WildlifeStudy$Common, "[']","")
WildlifeStudy$Common <- str_replace_all(WildlifeStudy$Common, "\\-.*", "")

#Adding specific species like "American Robin" into a bigger category called bird. The trail cameras were not designed for the identification of song birds, so we are removing this specificity. 

WildlifeStudy$Common <- str_replace_all(WildlifeStudy$Common, "Dark", "Bird")

Creating functions

#Creating the first function
#Objective: make a function that counts the number of observations per niche per month. Input being niche, put in niche and return the total Indiv. per month via date3.
CountNicheFreqWS <- function(WildlifeStudy, InputNiche){
  b <- WildlifeStudy %>% group_by(WildlifeStudy$date3, WildlifeStudy$Area) 
  c <- sum(b$Indiv.[b$Niche == InputNiche],na.rm = TRUE)
d <- (summarise(b,sum=sum(Indiv.[b$Niche == InputNiche],na.rm= TRUE)))
  return(d)
}
#testing function!!!
PreyFreqWS <- CountNicheFreqWS(WildlifeStudy, "Prey")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
PredaFreqWS <- CountNicheFreqWS(WildlifeStudy, "Predator")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
MezoFreqWS <- CountNicheFreqWS(WildlifeStudy, "Mesocarnivore")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
HumanFreqWS <- CountNicheFreqWS(WildlifeStudy, "Human")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
DomesticFreqWS <- CountNicheFreqWS(WildlifeStudy, "Domestic")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)

#Make function for camera count - Shiny base. This function works by inputting a niche, and the return gives you the total amount of observations for each niche by each camera and date.
CountCamFreq <- function(WildlifeStudy, InputNiche){
  a <- WildlifeStudy %>% group_by(WildlifeStudy$date3, WildlifeStudy$CamNumber1) 
  c <- sum(a$Indiv.[a$Niche == InputNiche],na.rm = TRUE)
d <- (summarise(a,sum=sum(Indiv.[a$Niche == InputNiche],na.rm= TRUE)))
  return(d)}

#Creating niche-camera subsets and renaming columns for organization.
PredatorCam <- CountCamFreq(WildlifeStudy, "Predator")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
names(PredatorCam)[1] <- "Date3" 
names(PredatorCam)[2] <- "Camera" 
names(PredatorCam)[3] <- "PredatorSum" 

PreyCam <- CountCamFreq(WildlifeStudy, "Prey")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
names(PreyCam)[1] <- "Date3" 
names(PreyCam)[2] <- "Camera" 
names(PreyCam)[3] <- "PreySum" 

MesoCam <- CountCamFreq(WildlifeStudy, "Mesocarnivore")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
names(MesoCam)[1] <- "Date3" 
names(MesoCam)[2] <- "Camera" 
names(MesoCam)[3] <- "MesoSum" 

HumanCam <- CountCamFreq(WildlifeStudy, "Human")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
names(HumanCam)[1] <- "Date3" 
names(HumanCam)[2] <- "Camera" 
names(HumanCam)[3] <- "HumanSum" 

DomesticCam <- CountCamFreq(WildlifeStudy, "Domestic")
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'WildlifeStudy$date3' (override with `.groups` argument)
names(DomesticCam)[1] <- "Date3" 
names(DomesticCam)[2] <- "Camera" 
names(DomesticCam)[3] <- "DometicSum" 

#Creating sum dataset used for Shiny app, this tells the program what data to look for and where to look for it within one data set.
